ef="/2019/organising-committee">Organising Committee</a></li><li class="index-2 last"><a title='Programme Committee' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/programme-committee">Programme Committee</a></li></ul></li><li class="index-6 last active"><a title='Details about sponsoring the symposium' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/sponsorship">Sponsors</a></li></ul><!--<form method="get" action="/2019/search" class="form-block nav-search"><input type="search" class="form-control nav-search-input pull-right" name="search" placeholder="Search…" value=""></form>--></nav></div></div></header><div class="row"><div class="main-container container-fluid"><div class="main row p-md-4 pt-sm-2 p-sm-1 pt-2 p-0 shadow"><div class="breadcrumb-container col-12"><nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="shadow rounded"><ol class="breadcrumb"><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/2019/">Halfway to the Future</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Sponsors</li></ol></nav></div><div class="col-12"><h1>Sponsors</h1></div><div class="col-xl-9 col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-12"><article><div data-bolt-field="teaser"><div><p>We are incredibly grateful to the organisations that have chosen to sponsor Halfway to the Future.</p></div></div><div class="card record-card d-none" data-bolt-field="body"><div class="card-body"><h5 class="card-title">Sponsor Halfway to the Future</h5><p>Sponsorship is an ideal opportunity to demonstrate your organisation’s commitment and research collaboration in the field of HCI and design-based research, as well as raising awareness of your products or services. If you are interested in sponsoring Halfway to the Future, please email <a href="mailto:sponsorship@halfwaytothefuture.org" title="Email Stuart Reeves for more information on sponsorsing the symposium">Stuart Reeves, our Sponsorship Chair</a> for details. We have multiple sponsorship tiers and can also create a bespoke sponsorship package for you.</p></div></div><div data-bolt-field="body"class=""><div><p><strong>Platinum Sponsors</strong><br></p><ul><li><a href="https://sigchi.org" title="The Association of Computing Machinery Special Interest Group on Computer-Human Interaction website">ACM SIGCHI</a></li><li><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/science" title="The University of Nottingham Faculty of Science website">University of Nottingham Faculty of Science</a></li><li><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/research/research-areas/creative-and-digital/index.aspx" title="The University of Nottingham Creative and Digital IRC website">University of Nottingham Creative and Digital Interdisciplinary Research Cluster</a></li></ul><p><strong>Gold Sponsors</strong><br></p><ul><li><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/" title="The Microsoft Research website">Microsoft Research</a></li><li><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/research/beacons-of-excellence/smart-products/index.aspx" title="The University of Nottingham Smart Products Beacon website">University of Nottingham Smart Products Beacon</a></li></ul><p><strong>Partners</strong><br></p><ul><li><a href="http://www.mrl.nott.ac.uk/" title="The Mixed Reality Laboratory website">Mixed Reality Lab</a></li></ul></div></div></article></div><aside class="col-xl-3 col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-12"><div class="card shadow rounded" class="p-2"><div class="card-body"><h5 class="card-title">Programme</h5><p>The symposium programme, with details of all keynotes, talks, posters, panels, and demos is online now. </p><a href="/2019/programme" class="card-link" title="Browse the programme">Programme</a></div></div></aside><div class="col-12 sponsors light"><p><strong>With thanks to our sponsors:</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/" title="University of Nottingham"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/partner-uon-black.png" alt="University of Nottingham logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://sigchi.org/" title="ACM SIGCHI"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/sponsor-sigchi-black.png" alt="SIGCHI logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/" title="Microsoft Research"><img src="/2019/files/2019-10/sponsor-microsoft-black.png" alt="Microsoft logo" /></a></p></div><div class="col-12 sponsors dark"><p><strong>With thanks to our sponsors:</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/" title="University of Nottingham"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/partner-uon-white.png" alt="University of Nottingham logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://sigchi.org/" title="ACM SIGCHI"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/sponsor-sigchi-white.png" alt="SIGCHI logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/" title="Microsoft Research"><img src="/2019/files/2019-10/sponsor-microsoft-white.png" alt="Microsoft logo" /></a></p></div></div></div></div></div><footer class="container"><div class="row"><div class="footer-container container-fluid"><div class="row d-flex flex-column justify-content-center flex-md-row"><p>© Halfway to the Future 2019.</p><p>Read our <a href="/2019/privacy-policy" title="HttF Privacy Policy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p><p>Follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/httfsymposium" title="@httfsymposium on Twitter">Twitter</a>.</p><hr><p>Designed by <a href="https://www.porcheron.uk/" title="Martin Porcheron">Martin Porcheron</a>.</p></div></div></div></footer></body></html>